    New in Scopus: Preprints

    We have added preprints to author profiles to help you discover the latest contributions of a researcher. Preprints are non-peer reviewed publications and are directly derived from arXiv, bioRxiv, ChemRxiv, medRxiv and SSRN servers and follow their respective curation policies. Preprints do not affect existing publication and citation metrics in Scopus.

    Scopus covers preprints from 2017 onwards.    Â Learn more
